  "prompt": "How much do furniture salesmen make?",
  "response": "The earnings of furniture salesmen can vary widely depending on several factors such as:\n\n1. Location\n2. Experience\n3. Commission structure\n4. Type of furniture store\n5. Sales volume\n\nAccording to the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics, as of May 2020:\n- Median annual wage for retail sales workers (including furniture salespeople): Around $25,940\n- Lowest 10%: Less than $20,450\n- Highest 10%: More than $45,000\n\nCommissioned salespeople in high-end furniture stores or those selling expensive items can potentially earn significantly more, sometimes exceeding $60,000-$80,000 annually with strong sales performance.\n\nTypical compensation often includes:\n- Base salary\n- Commission\n- Bonuses\n- Potential benefits\n\nEarnings can be higher in:\n- Luxury furniture stores\n- Urban areas\n- Stores with higher-priced merchandise\n\nKeep in mind that these figures are approximate and can change over time and by specific market conditions.",
